var <variable_name> = <value>;
Variables must be declared before use.
Variables store integer values (0-255).
Only var keyword is used for declaration.
Example:

simplelang
Copy
Edit
var x = 10;
var y = 20;
2. Assignments
Syntax:

simplelang
Copy
Edit
<variable_name> = <expression>;
Variables can be assigned new values.
Expressions may involve arithmetic operations.
Example:

simplelang
Copy
Edit
x = y + 5;
3. Arithmetic Operations
Supported Operators:

+ (Addition)
- (Subtraction)
* (Multiplication)
/ (Integer Division)
Syntax:

simplelang
Copy
Edit
<variable_name> = <expression>;
Example:

simplelang
Copy
Edit
var a = 10;
var b = 5;
var c = a + b;  // c = 15
var d = c - 2;  // d = 13
4. Conditional Statements
Syntax:

simplelang
Copy
Edit
if (<condition>) {
    <statements>;
} else {
    <statements>;
}
Supports if-else statements.
Conditions can use ==, !=, >, <, >=, <=.
Example:

simplelang
Copy
Edit
var x = 10;
if (x > 5) {
    x = x - 2;
} else {
    x = x + 2;
}
5. Loops (While)
Syntax:

simplelang
Copy
Edit
while (<condition>) {
    <statements>;
}
Loops execute while the condition is true.
Example:

simplelang
Copy
Edit
var count = 0;
while (count < 5) {
    count = count + 1;
}
6. Input and Output
Syntax:

simplelang
Copy
Edit
print(<expression>);
read(<variable_name>);
print displays a value.
read takes user input.
Example:

simplelang
Copy
Edit
var age;
read(age);
print(age);
7. Full Example Program
simplelang
Copy
Edit
var a = 10;
var b = 20;
var c = a + b;

if (c > 25) {
    print(c);
} else {
    print(0);
}

var count = 0;
while (count < 3) {
    print(count);
    count = count + 1;
}
